<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-24T07:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-24T07:54:00-05:00" n="992" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d992">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7490F/5–2445: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-24T16:00:00+03:06">May 24,
                                    1945—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 26—3:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>216. ReDept 136 Apr [<hi rend="italic">May</hi>] 17 to London [<hi rend="italic">Jidda</hi>].<note n="20" xml:id="d992fn20">Same as
                                telegram 3898 to London, <ref target="#pg_1021">p.
                                1021</ref>.</note> Saudi Govt informs me they consider that they
                            have already reserved all rights of <pb facs="1035" n="1023" xml:id="pg_1023"/> modification of contract at any time in future by
                            virtue of their notice given Nov 21, 1944. They have today so officially
                            notified British Govt and Cable and Wireless Co.</p>
                        <p>I am transmitting proposal in Depts No. 145, May 22, regarding which,
                            however, Saudi Govt assures me June 1 date is of no consequence as they
                            are certain of their freedom to establish any external communications
                            they wish.</p>
                        <p>Rptd London.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>